The paper focuses on the application of deep learning models to neuroimaging data, specifically functional Magnetic Resonance Imaging (fMRI) data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of long short-term memory (LSTM) models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of analyzing high-dimensional and low-sample size datasets, which are common issues in the field of Neuroscience (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of layer-wise relevance propagation (LRP) for interpretability, which is a technique commonly used in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.CL, in that order.
